subject: p13291370
Findings: Portable AP radiograph of the chest was reviewed in comparison to. The multifocal opacities on the current study appear to be progressed as compared to prior examination concerning for multifocal infection. There is small amount of right pleural effusion, slightly increased since the prior study. No definitive evidence of pulmonary edema is present, but it cannot be entirely excluded and reassessment of the patient after diuresis is recommended. The position of the pacemaker is slightly unclear, and although unchanged since prior examinations, still most likely is in the right ventricle.
